‚úÖ How I Deploy an Assignment Using Docker, Rancher Desktop, WSL & Azure

1Ô∏è‚É£ Develop the Project (Local Machine)
I first complete my Python/Flask/FastAPI/Node project on my local machine.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Install Required Tools
I install:
WSL ‚Üí Linux environment inside Windows
Rancher Desktop ‚Üí provides the Docker engine (nerdctl)
Docker CLI / Nerdctl ‚Üí to build and run containers
Azure CLI ‚Üí to deploy my container

3Ô∏è‚É£ Write a Dockerfile
I create a Dockerfile inside the project folder.
Example:
FROM python:3.10-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
EXPOSE 5000
CMD ["python", "app.py"]

This tells Docker:
which Python image to use
install requirements
run the app

4Ô∏è‚É£ Build Docker Image (WSL Terminal)
Inside WSL terminal:
nerdctl build -t myapp:latest .

This creates a docker image.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Run the Docker Container Locally
To check if it works:
nerdctl run -p 5000:5000 myapp:latest

Now I open browser and check:
üëâ http://localhost:5000
This confirms the image works.

6Ô∏è‚É£ Push the Image to Azure Container Registry (ACR)
Step 6.1 ‚Äì Login
az login
Step 6.2 ‚Äì Login to ACR
az acr login --name <my-acr-name>
Step 6.3 ‚Äì Tag the Image
ACR images need a special tag:
nerdctl tag myapp:latest <my-acr-name>.azurecr.io/myapp:latest
Step 6.4 ‚Äì Push the Image
nerdctl push <my-acr-name>.azurecr.io/myapp:latest

Now the image is stored on Azure.

7Ô∏è‚É£ Create Azure Container App Environment
az containerapp env create \
  --name my-env \
  --resource-group my-rg \
  --location centralindia

8Ô∏è‚É£ Deploy the Application on Azure Container Apps
az containerapp create \
  --name myapp \
  --resource-group my-rg \
  --environment my-env \
  --image <my-acr-name>.azurecr.io/myapp:latest \
  --ingress external \
  --target-port 5000


Azure assigns a public URL.
This URL is the live deployment.

9Ô∏è‚É£ Verify Deployment

I open Azure Portal ‚Üí go to Container Apps ‚Üí copy the URL and test it.


You can speak like this:

‚ÄúI develop the project locally, then I use WSL and Rancher Desktop to build a Docker image.
I create a Dockerfile, build the image using nerdctl, and run it locally to test.
After that, I tag the image and push it to Azure Container Registry.
Then I create a Container App Environment in Azure and deploy the container from ACR.
Azure gives me a public URL where my application runs.‚Äù



‚úÖ TOP Docker Interview Questions (Simple Answers)
1Ô∏è‚É£ What is Docker?

Simple:
Docker is a tool that packages your application and all its dependencies into one small box called a container, so it runs the same everywhere.

2Ô∏è‚É£ What is a Container?

A small lightweight environment where your app runs.
It contains only what your app needs ‚Üí fast & portable.

3Ô∏è‚É£ What is an Image?

A template or blueprint used to create containers.
Like a photo ‚Üí container is a photocopy.

4Ô∏è‚É£ What is a Dockerfile?

A text file that tells Docker how to build an image.

Example: install Python, copy files, run app.

5Ô∏è‚É£ What are Docker Volumes?

A way to store data outside of containers, so data is safe even if the container is deleted.

6Ô∏è‚É£ What is Docker Compose?

A tool that helps you run multiple containers together (e.g., app + database) using one YAML file.

7Ô∏è‚É£ What is the difference: Image vs Container?

Image ‚Üí blueprint

Container ‚Üí running instance of that image

8Ô∏è‚É£ What is Docker Hub?

Online store for Docker images (public or private).

9Ô∏è‚É£ How do you build a Docker image?
docker build -t myapp .

üîü How do you run a Docker container?
docker run -p 5000:5000 myapp

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ What is the purpose of EXPOSE in Dockerfile?

Tells which port the container uses.

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ What is ENTRYPOINT vs CMD?

ENTRYPOINT ‚Üí main command

CMD ‚Üí default arguments
Easy rule: ENTRYPOINT is fixed, CMD can change.

1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ What is the difference: Docker vs Virtual Machine?

Docker uses containers ‚Üí lightweight, fast

VM runs full OS ‚Üí heavy, slow

1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ What is Layering in Docker?

Each instruction in Dockerfile creates a layer.
These layers are cached ‚Üí builds are faster.

1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ What is Docker Registry?

A storage where images are saved (Docker Hub, Azure ACR).

1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ What is ACR (Azure Container Registry)?

Azure‚Äôs private Docker image store.

1Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ How do you push an image to Docker Hub or ACR?
docker push repo/image:tag

1Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ How do you check running containers?
docker ps

1Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ How do you stop a container?
docker stop <id>

2Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ What happens when a container stops?

The application inside stops running.
But image and data (volumes) remain.

2Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ What happens when you delete a container?

Only that running copy gets deleted.
Image stays.

2Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ What is the context in Docker build?

The folder contents sent to Docker engine for building.

2Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ What is .dockerignore?

File that tells Docker ‚Äúignore these files when building.‚Äù

Example:
.env, __pycache__, node_modules

2Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ What is multi-stage build?

Use multiple FROM in Dockerfile to reduce final image size.

2Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ What is Port Mapping?

Connecting container port to host port.

Example:
-p 5000:5000

2Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ How do you see logs of a container?
docker logs <container_id>

2Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ What is the use of WORKDIR in Dockerfile?

Sets the default working directory inside the container.

2Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ What is a base image?

The starting image used in Dockerfile (e.g., python:3.10-slim).

2Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ What is tagging of an image?

Giving version/name to an image.

Example:
myapp:v1

3Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ What is the difference: ADD vs COPY?

COPY ‚Üí simple file copy

ADD ‚Üí can download URLs or extract tar files
Use COPY mostly (best practice).

3Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ How do you remove all containers?
docker rm -f $(docker ps -aq)

3Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ How do you remove images?
docker rmi <image>

3Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ What is Docker Network?

Containers can communicate with each other inside a virtual network.

3Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ What is Bridge Network?

Default network; containers can talk to each other.

3Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ What is Host Network?

Container uses the host machine‚Äôs network directly.

3Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ What is bind mount?

Mounting a folder from your machine into container.

3Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ How do you inspect a running container?
docker inspect <id>

3Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ How do you exec into a container?
docker exec -it <id> bash

3Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ Difference between Container Restart Policies?

no ‚Üí don‚Äôt restart

always ‚Üí restart always

on-failure ‚Üí restart only if crash

4Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ What is OCI?

Open Container Initiative ‚Äì standards for containers & images.

4Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ What is Rancher Desktop?

A tool that gives Docker/nerdctl engine on Windows (alternative to Docker Desktop).

4Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ What is nerdctl?

Docker-compatible CLI provided by Rancher Desktop.

4Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ How do you deploy Docker containers to Azure?

Steps:

Build Image

Push to ACR

Deploy using Azure Container Apps / Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)

4Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ What is Image ID and Container ID?

Unique identifiers for image or container.

4Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ Why do we use slim images?

They are lightweight ‚Üí faster & more secure.

4Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ What is ENV in Dockerfile?

Sets environment variables.

4Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ What is HEALTHCHECK?

Tells Docker how to check if the app inside container is healthy.

4Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ What is BuildKit?

Modern backend for faster and parallel Docker builds.

4Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ What is the lifecycle of a container?

Image ‚Üí Create ‚Üí Start ‚Üí Run ‚Üí Stop ‚Üí Remove.

5Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ What kind of projects have you Dockerized?

Always mention:

Flask API

Node API

React + Backend

ML model API
